This directory contains host-side unit tests for the esp32-cam-rtsp firmware.
Tests use the Unity framework (third-party/unity/) and GCC mock stubs.

## Running tests — Option A: PlatformIO native env (recommended)

Requires the native platform to be installed once:
    pio pkg install -g -p native

Run all host-test suites:
    pio test -e native

Run a single suite:
    pio test -e native -f native/test_nvs_config

## Running tests — Option B: GNU Make (legacy)

    make -f test/Makefile

Produces three test runner binaries and executes them sequentially.
Use this option if PlatformIO is not available or for CI pipelines
that do not use PlatformIO.

## Test suite layout

    test/native/<suite>/     PlatformIO suite directories (copies of test/components/)
    test/components/<suite>/ Canonical test source files (referenced by the Makefile)
    test/mocks/              Mock headers and .c stubs for ESP-IDF APIs

Files in test/native/ are copies of the canonical sources in test/components/.
Keep them in sync manually when modifying test cases.

## Custom test runner

    test/test_custom_runner.py

Disables PlatformIO's built-in throwtheswitch/Unity package and injects
third-party/unity/unity.c plus the correct component sources and mock stubs
for each suite. Required to avoid linker conflicts (multiple definition of
UnityBegin) between PlatformIO's auto-injected Unity and third-party/unity/.